commit.message: Handle KillException if a thread is killed while in Socket.select.  This previously led to a segfault.

Reduce the size of a writable code area if we need to use a shadow area and
the size is too big for the temporary file space.  This can occur on NetBSD.
Fixes #191.
Some tidying up and simplification.
Add some extra tests for IEEEReal.scan/fromString from pull request 188.  Fix error in IEEEReal.scan.
Fix handling overflow in exponent in IEEEReal.fromString (#182).  Includes the examples as a regression test.
Include tests from #183 now it should be fixed.
Fix two warnings.  Remove unused static definition for Real_Conv and remove assertion that produces warning of constant overflow in 32-in-64.
Remove regression test.  It doesn't work if int is arbitrary precision and it is very sensitive to small changes.
Remove RTS function to convert a string to a real since it's now implemented in ML.

Implement Ryu code to convert decimal representation to reals.  Remove explicit use of FixedInt in the bit representations and use the default
int.
Use word shifts for IntInf.<< if the argument is short and the highest set bit will not be shifted into the sign bit or out of the word.
Fold constant expressions involving shifts and Log2Word.
Remove PolyRealBoxedToLongInt from RTS since it's now implemented in ML.
Implement conversion to arbitrary precision within ML.  There is a separate implementation for Real32.real rather than converting to Real.real.
Bug fix for X86 code-generator.  If a work register is required for a JumpLoop it must be distinct from target registers.
Fix a couple of problems with the GMP version of left shift.
Implement arbitrary precision shifts in the RTS rather than using multiplication for IntInf.<< and IntInf.~>>.
Remove unnecessary test and add comment.
Add example definition of RealNumbersAsBits using PackReal(32)Big.
Fixes for when int is LargeInt.int.
Tidy up non-exact conversion.  Add ".0" to general format output if there is no decimal point or exponent.
Add missing const specifier.

Use snprintf for scientific, fixed and general formatting of real numbers.  Remove ML code to format them based on the exact conversion since
that doesn't produce the correct result.
Rename the conversion functions and include the IEEEReal class in the result.  This allows them to work for non-finite values as well.
Remove unused variables.
Fix incomplete changes to type constraints.
Combine the float and double conversion code after the first step.  Fix bug in floatExponent for 32-bit platforms.  Use Boost licence for RealToDecimalConversion.
Remove print statement.  This now succeeds.
Merge branch 'IEEERealFixes' into RealNumberConversion
Move the test code to avoid a merge conflict.
